Downdetector.co.za reported the United Kingdom, the USA and most parts of Europe as areas most hard hit by the outage. JOHANNESBURG - Facebook, Instagram, and WhatsApp were seemingly unresponsive on Wednesday both in South Africa and around the world. South African users found sanctuary on twitter as they expressed despair and heartbreak saying image, audio and voice note files could not be downloaded on WhatsApp and Facebook. Facebook says they are aware of the problems and are working to get things back to normal as quickly as possible. Social media service website Downdetector.co.za reported worldwide outages and interruptions with minimum yet visible reports coming from SA. The site also showed the United Kingdom, the USA and most parts of Europe as areas most hard hit by the outage. The most reported problems for WhatsApp were receiving messages while Instagram had news feed issues.